description.narrative: The Multi Sectoral National Plan of Action for Nutrition (MS-NPAN) costing and budget briefs for prioritized states and regions were drafted with substantial technical and financial support from UNICEF and National Nutrition Centre (NNC). UNICEF has been chairing SUN network, ensuring that the agreed framework of action for maternal nutrition and complementary feeding for Myanmar is implemented with the MS-NPAN. A stronger coordination mechanism and linkages with maternal and child cash transfer (MCCT), Early Childhood Development (ECD) , WASH, food systems and education was realized for maintaining essential nutrition services as response to COVID-19 pandemic. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/07/2020
